But if nothing lie beyond this bounded material sys- tem, then it is bounded by nothing; and if it be bounded by nothing then, again, has it no bounds whatever; and of course there would be nothing to resist the farther flight of the arrow. So that the force of our poet’s appeal still remains uninvalidated.
